defaults, Wells and Lee the cou
defaultrt ruled
default that the rights of three prisoners 
defaultserving indeterminate sentence for pubic protection (IPPs) 
defaulthad been breached 
defaultas
default reasonable provision for their rehabilitation was not made. The lawfulness of indefinite detention based on a risk to the public has
default to be balanced against whether the risk is addressed in detention. The prison service has made efforts to address this situation but these have 
defaultnot gone far enough. The government should now re
defaultview all post tariff IPP cases (
defaultaround 3,500 people
default)
default and reassess risk, allocate additional offender management resources and prioritise courses and offending behaviour work. The Secretary of State should introduce new guidance and directions for the Parole Board to assess risk and for the release test, as 
defaultintroduced in the L
defaultegal 
defaultA
defaultid, 
defaultS
defaultentencing and 
defaultP
defaultunishment of 
defaultO
defaultffenders
default Act. A new release test should be introduced, that puts the obligation on the state to prove that someone is still a risk if the state is opposing release.
default&#xa0;
defaultThe 
defaultN
defaultational 
defaultO
defaultffender 
defaultM
